Stay at home
Only go outside for food, health reasons or work (but only if you cannot work from home)
If you go out, stay 2 metres (6ft) away from other people at all times
Wash your hands as soon as you get home
Do not meet others, even friends or family.
You can spread the virus even if you don’t have symptoms.

There are currently no commercial flights in to or out of Botswana. Medevac flights remain possible. The Botswana authorities have also closed land border posts with neighbouring countries. Only citizens and residents will be allowed entry.
The South African Government announced on 25 March the closure of South African airspace to commercial airlines from midnight on 26 March until at least 16 April, as part of further efforts to contain the spread of coronavirus. This has affected flights in to and out of Botswana. Follow our travel advice for South Africa for information on South African entry requirements, and consult your nearest South African High Commission.
We know this is concerning for British people trying to leave Botswana. The UK government is working closely with airlines and the Botswana authorities on commercial options for you to return to the UK as soon as possible.
If you are a British national currently visiting Botswana and would like to return home to the UK, the British High Commission can update you when flight options become available by adding you to a mailing list. If you would like to receive these updates, please email Gaborone.Enquiries@fco.gov.uk with the subject heading ‘return from Botswana’ and include your: name, mobile telephone number, location, and any other relevant information. Please also check the British High Commission’s latest updates on Facebook and Twitter.
While you are in Botswana, please continue to follow the advice of the Government of Botswana and local authorities; you can find the latest updates on the Government of Botswana’s Facebook page. Please also subscribe to our travel advice.
Further information
See additional advice on making travel plans to return to the UK, or what to do if you cannot depart immediately.
